        "\n",
        "## 18.20 Calibration diagnostics\n",
        "\n",
        "A probabilistic forecast is calibrated if events predicted to happen with probability $p$ happen about proportion $p$ of the time.\n",
        "\n",
        "For intervals, calibration means\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbb P(L_{t,h}\\le Y_{t+h}\\le U_{t,h})\\approx 1-\\alpha.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "For a full forecast CDF $F_{t,h}$, the probability integral transform is\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "U_{t,h}=F_{t,h}(Y_{t+h}).\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "If the predictive CDFs are calibrated and continuous, then $U_{t,h}$ should be approximately uniform on $[0,1]$.\n",
        "\n",
        "Common diagnostic plots include:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. empirical coverage by horizon;\n",
        "2. average interval width by horizon;\n",
        "3. coverage by season, regime, or demand level;\n",
        "4. PIT histogram;\n",
